 023:     """
 024:     Circle section fibers generate
 025:     Input:ax-axes
 026:           d0-concreate cover length (m)
 027:           outD-outside diameter (m)
 028:           inD-inner diameter (m)
 029:           if inD==None,the section is solid circle, otherwise is torus
 030:     #######################---solid section circle example---#########################
 031:     from fiberGenerate import CircleSection
 032:     import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
 033:     fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))
 034:     ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
 035:     outbarD = 0.03  # outside bar diameter
 036:     outbarDist = 0.15  # outside bar space
 037:     d0 = 0.06  # the thinckness of the cover concrete
 038:     eleSize = 0.15  # the size of core concrete fiber
 039:     coverSize = 0.15  # the size of cover concrete fiber
 040:     outD = 3  # the diameter of the outside circle
 041:     circleInstance = CircleSection(ax, d0, outD)  # call the circle section generate class
 042:     circleInstance.initSectionPlot()  # plot profile of the circle
 043:     coreFiber = circleInstance.coreMesh(eleSize)  # generate core concrete fiber elements [(x1,y1,area1),...]
 044:     coverFiber = circleInstance.coverMesh(coverSize)  # generate cover concrete fiber elements [(x1,y1,area1),...]
 045:     barFiber = circleInstance.barMesh(outbarD, outbarDist)  # generate the bar fiber elements [(x1,y1,area1),...]
 046:     plt.show()
 047:     #######################---torus section example---#########################
 048:     from fiberGenerate import CircleSection
 049:     import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
 050:     fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))
 051:     ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
 052:     outbarD = 0.03  # outside bar diameter
 053:     outbarDist = 0.15  # outside bar space
 054:     inBarD = 0.03  # inside bar diameter
 055:     inBarDist = 0.15  # inside bar space
 056:     d0 = 0.1  # the thinckness of the cover concrete
 057:     coreSize = 0.15  # the size of core concrete fiber
 058:     coverSize = 0.15  # the size of cover concrete fiber
 059:     outD = 3  # the diameter of the outside circle
 060:     inD = 1  # the diameter of the inner circle
 061:     circleInstance = CircleSection(ax, d0, outD, inD)  # call the circle section generate class
 062:     circleInstance.initSectionPlot()  # plot profile of the circle
 063:     coreFiber = circleInstance.coreMesh(coreSize)  # generate core concrete fiber elements
 064:     coverFiber = circleInstance.coverMesh(coverSize)  # generate cover concrete fiber elements
 065:     barFiber = circleInstance.barMesh(outbarD, outbarDist, inBarD, inBarDist)  # generate the bar fiber elements
 066:     plt.show()
 067:     """
 068:     ####################################################
